Episode 3 of Senior Speak is here! In this episode, we talk mindfulness with Mrs. Benedict and interview seniors Kaelyn McClain and Stephen Frost. These seniors continue to amaze & inspire us:

[https://anchor.fm/efpodcast2020/episodes/Senior-Speak--Episode-3-ee2eom](https://anchor.fm/efpodcast2020/episodes/Senior-Speak--Episode-3-ee2eom)

CONGRATULATIONS to Travis Evans, 2020 Elizabeth Forward High School recipient of the Eric Hussey Memorial Scholarship ($3700). Eric Hussey Memorial Scholarship - The purpose is to honor the memory and legacy of Eric Hussey and providing a scholarship to a MOST IMPROVED graduating senior. TRAVIS EVANS has demonstrated a positive outlook and continual improvement throughout the school year in the areas of: academic achievement, work ethic, participation, encouragement and support to fellow students. Also, in addition to his involvement in the community as a Volunteer Firefighter at Blaine Hill Fire Department. His future plans are to enter into the trades. Thank you to everyone who has supported Eric's fund.

Elizabeth Forward SD
April 7 at 9:58 AM ·

Triple B Farms is HIRING this Spring!

Each year the farm hires approximately 15 students to help pick our berry crops and work around the farm. It is a great first job experience for students!
Requirements:
Must be 14 years old or older by June 1st.
Must have parental permission.
Must have dependable ride/rideshare for work schedule.
Picking Days/Hours: Approximately every other day June & July; typically 7:30-11am. Varies with crop and weather.
Other hours vary, but will be during normal work day.
Please go to: www.triplebfarms.com and click on CONTACT/We are HIRING. You will get a drop down work application.
We must receive all applications by April 30. Training meetings will occur in May.
For any further questions, please call 724.258.3557 or email: sue@triplebfarms.com

Elizabeth Forward SD
March 20 at 11:02 AM ·

We hope you and your family are doing well and everyone is in our thoughts and prayers!

In the interest of student, staff and community health/safety, the Elizabeth Forward School District will continue with Virtual Instructional Days until further notice. Our Virtual Instructional Days will satisfy the requirement of a 180-day school year and our goal is to finish the school year approximately June 4, 2020.

The District will continue to provide breakfast and lunch for each student. Please register for the meals on www.efsd.net and you only need to sign up once to receive meals. Meals can be picked up at the Elizabeth Learning Center (207 South 3rd Avenue, Elizabeth, PA 15037) or Elizabeth Forward Middle School (401 Rock Run Road, Elizabeth, PA 15037) between 11:00 am and 12:00 pm.

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this challenging time. As additional information becomes available, we will keep you updated. We are EFstrong!
